The following code from com.atlassian.confluence.plugin.descriptor.web.descriptors.ConfluenceWebItemModuleDescriptor should first test for the existence of the delegate decorated descriptor's icon, otherwise from a velocity template, there is no viable test for the existence of an icon.  The Decorated descriptor is not a public method so there is also no workaround.

{code:java}
    public WebIcon getIcon()
    {
        return new ConfluenceWebIcon(((WebItemModuleDescriptor) getDecoratedDescriptor()).getIcon());
    }
{code}

