The JS AJAX function which auto-saves pages from the edit screen, does not save the Location information. inexperienced users (of which there are many) then resume editing their draft, and cannot work out why their pages are in the wrong place (if they even notice).

Ideally the autosave functionality should save the location information with the draft.

Verified in IE7 and FF2.0.

The excerpt include macro can't break the text properly into next lines when the excerpt macro defined in another page with line break. Besides, the link defined in the excerpt macro doesn't work as well.

Steps to reproduce:

# Create a page name *Page A* with the following excerpt macro
{noformat}
{excerpt}
Line1
Line2
Line3
[Link to a Page]
{excerpt}
{noformat}
# Create another page named *Page B* and use the excerpt include macro within an excerpt macro
{noformat}
{excerpt}
{excerpt-include:Page A}
{excerpt}
{noformat}

You should be able to see the Page B content shown in one line instead of breaking into new lines which is not matching with the original page content. It's working fine in Confluence version 2.6.1.

