JIRA requires that the username used during login match the case on file for that account.  Confluence performs a toLowerCase() on login.  In order to ensure consistency across Atlassian applications, would it be possible to remove this please?  It used to make sense for Confluence when it only used internal user management which requires all usernames to be lowercase on creation.

Thanks,
Donna

